# Security Guidelines

## API Key Management
- LLM API keys must be stored as environment variables
- Never commit API keys to version control
- Backend must securely handle all API key usage

## Input Validation
- All user inputs must be validated using Pydantic models
- Implement rate limiting for API endpoints
- Validate content length and field count to prevent abuse

## PII Handling
- Be cautious with Personally Identifiable Information (PII)
- Implement proper data sanitization
- Follow data protection best practices

## Environment Configuration
- Use secure environment variables for sensitive configuration
- Keep production and development configurations separate
- Follow the principle of least privilege
